      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-06-18T16:05:36Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDate>2017-12-04</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong></strong></p> <p>This bill requires the President to establish a commission called the "Anti-Bullying Roundtable" to study bullying in&nbsp;elementary and secondary schools in the United States.</p> <p>The roundtable must submit a report about best practices concerning bullying, including recommendations for: (1)&nbsp;combating bullying, (2) educating school officials to recognize bullying, and (3) helping parents to address the early warning signs of bullying with their children. </p>]]></text>
